 Macao'' and shoot the pilot the plane crashes, killing 26 of 27 people on board.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/17</date><description> A Douglas DC-6 carrying United Air Lines Flight 624 crashes near Mount Carmel, Pennsylvania, killing all 43 people on board.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/18</date><description> Malayan Emergency: A state of emergency is declared in the Malayan Union due to a communist insurgency.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/18</date><description> LP record ampndash Columbia Records introduced it's long playing 33 sup1/sup/sub3/sub rpm phonograph format.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/20</date><description> The U.S. Congress recesses for the remainder of 1948, after an overtime session closes at 7:00 a.m. D.C. time (to be shortly interrupted by Truman's recall from Congressional recess for July 20, 1948).</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/21</date><description> The Deutsche Mark becomes official currency of the future Federal Republic of Germany.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/22</date><description> The ship ''Empire Windrush'' brings a large group of Afro-Caribbean immigrants to Tilbury near London, the start of a large wave of immigration to Britain.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/22</date><description>Cold War: The Berlin Blockade begins.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/22</date><description>The first World Health Assembly of the World Health Organization is held in Geneva.</description><lang>en</lang><granularity>year</granularity></event><event><date>1948/06/26</date><description> William Shockley